From 1710cc300fd4f4e41f01ae6c2c7948fdfbfca012 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Max Furman <taygoth@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 29 May 2026 11:37:31 +0500
Subject: [PATCH 7/9] ASoC: codecs: add TAS2557 smart amplifier driver

Add a minimal Texas Instruments TAS2557 ASoC codec driver used by Xiaomi
Mi 8 speaker output.

The driver follows the legacy TI Android TAS2557 firmware format used by
the available tas2557_uCDSP.bin and tas2557_cal.bin files. Keep it
self-contained instead of depending on the newer TAS2781 tasdevice
firmware library, whose RCA/coef split and header layout do not match
these blobs.

This is primarily a Mobian/local port patch. It supports the validated
ASI1 playback path, firmware/config loading, calibration blob loading,
and runtime mute/unmute sequence needed for dipper bring-up.

Signed-off-by: Max Furman <taygoth@gmail.com>
---
 sound/soc/codecs/Kconfig   |   10 +
 sound/soc/codecs/Makefile  |    2 +
 sound/soc/codecs/tas2557.c | 1230 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 3 files changed, 1242 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 sound/soc/codecs/tas2557.c

